  "riddle": "1. Unearth the biography of the individual who stands tall at what height? Discover Joe Bretto’s stature and move forward.\n\n2. A crucial role in athletics involves overseeing all operations; how many languages are commonly linked with this position in sports management? \n\n3. This franchise calls a notable city in upstate New York its home. Can you identify the urban center where its players don their uniforms? \n\n4. One letter starts the name of this city — what is its position in the English alphabet? \n\n5. Within a larger league filled with talent, how many teams battle for victory at the Triple-A level of professional baseball?\n\n6. From the elevation of the Triple-A realm, how high above the sea does the ground rise? \n\n7. When discussing this professional category, what star rating do patrons award? \n\n8. Now combine the elevation you found in clue 6 with the rating you uncovered in clue 7. What is the absolute difference when you take 10 and subtract your combined value?\n\n9. The journey between Buffalo and Rochester marks a significant distance. In how many minutes can this trip by vehicle be completed?\n\n10. A binary puzzle awaits! What is the total count of 1-bits when the driving duration from clue 9 is translated into binary form? \n\n11. Focus on accommodation: how many places to stay can be found near Buffalo’s vibrant landscape? \n\n12. Finally, to wrap up your quest, add the two numbers yielded in clues 4 and 5 together, then find the modulus with 10. What single-digit result emerges from your calculation? \n\nYour answer is a single digit (0-9).",
